"async/go-loop" is a function that takes a channel, a function and a list of
items. It will call the function for each item in the list, passing the item
as an argument. The function will be called concurrently in its own thread.
The function passed to async/go-loop can return a future, which will be
immediately resolved, and then the next item in the list will be processed.

